00:49:44,597 --> 00:49:47,138
Well, you love the book that much.
You should have a copy of your own.

722
00:49:47,764 --> 00:49:50,225
-I can't pay you.
-It's a gift.

723
00:49:51,391 --> 00:49:52,724
You've gotten gifts before,
haven't you?

724
00:49:52,892 --> 00:49:53,975
It's been a while.

725
00:49:55,184 --> 00:49:58,519
-Well, it's my way of saying, thanks.
-For what?

726
00:49:59,686 --> 00:50:02,354
That somebody listens...
even if it's just one student.

727
00:50:03,230 --> 00:50:04,605
You're a good teacher, Mr. Carlson.

728
00:50:04,688 --> 00:50:06,896
Listen, we can discuss the book
on Friday in class if you...

729
00:50:07,313 --> 00:50:08,816
...think the Count can
hold their attention.

730
00:50:09,150 --> 00:50:10,315
He's got a shot.

731
00:50:11,149 --> 00:50:12,441
Any particular section
I should read from?

732
00:50:13,192 --> 00:50:15,859
That's easy...the part where
he escapes from prison.

733
00:50:29,532 --> 00:50:32,366
There you go, All Star.
Here's your locker room!

734
00:50:39,910 --> 00:50:44,412
It was only a game...just a touch
football game, nothing more.

735
00:50:45,246 --> 00:50:46,997
But a game I wish we
had never played.

736
00:50:48,039 --> 00:50:51,873
Guards against inmates.
The guards practiced four times a week.

737
00:50:52,707 --> 00:50:54,875
Our team was picked the
Monday before the game.

738
00:50:55,584 --> 00:50:57,083
We had a 2 hour practice.

739
00:50:58,001 --> 00:50:59,209
It didn't matter much.

740
00:50:59,584 --> 00:51:02,585
We weren't supposed to win.
We were just supposed to show up.

741
00:51:03,252 --> 00:51:04,713
Who's the toughest guy here?

742
00:51:05,713 --> 00:51:06,921
How do you mean, tough?

743
00:51:07,421 --> 00:51:09,088
Who can talk and have
everyone listening?

744
00:51:09,256 --> 00:51:11,256
Rizzo. Black kid over there.

745
00:51:13,215 --> 00:51:16,716
Michael saw an opening...a chance
to bring the game to our level.

746
00:51:16,883 --> 00:51:20,885
Even out the field. But he needed help.
He needed Rizzo.

747
00:51:21,718 --> 00:51:25,803
Black kid with an Italian name.
With him on our side, we had a chance.

748
00:51:26,721 --> 00:51:29,722
Look, white boy, I don't know
what you play in the streets.

749
00:51:29,888 --> 00:51:32,140
I don't care. But in here,
the guards call the play...

750
00:51:32,307 --> 00:51:33,931
...and the play calls for
them to win the game.

751
00:51:34,015 --> 00:51:34,766
Why?

752
00:51:35,099 --> 00:51:36,099
Look man...

753
00:51:36,600 --> 00:51:38,099
...guards stay clear of me, all right?

754
00:51:38,266 --> 00:51:39,766
They stay back and let me do my time.

755
00:51:40,100 --> 00:51:41,935
If I play that game and I
put a hurt on one of them...

756
00:51:42,102 --> 00:51:43,728
...they just might change my cushion.

757
00:51:43,936 --> 00:51:47,103
I'm not saying we gotta win.
I just don't want to take a beating.

758
00:51:47,645 --> 00:51:48,604
You do every day.

759
00:51:49,313 --> 00:51:52,605
-Why is Saturday special?
-'Cause on Saturday, we can hit back.

760
00:51:55,773 --> 00:51:58,815
They don't fuck with you like they do us,
but they fuck with you another way!

761
00:51:58,983 --> 00:52:00,233
You're just an animal to them.

762
00:52:01,400 --> 00:52:04,067
-I don't give a fuck!
-Yeah, you do.

763
00:52:04,444 --> 00:52:06,944
And beating them on Saturday
is not gonna change a thing.

764
00:52:07,821 --> 00:52:08,987
Then why, white boy, why?

765
00:52:09,155 --> 00:52:13,530
To make them feel what we feel
...just for a couple of hours.

766
00:52:15,739 --> 00:52:17,532
Now, don't try anything funny, Sambo.

767
00:52:17,741 --> 00:52:19,867
Nobody will get hurt.
You know what I'm saying?

768
00:52:20,284 --> 00:52:21,201
I call heads.

769
00:52:24,326 --> 00:52:26,328
He called heads.
It is a head.

770
00:52:28,285 --> 00:52:29,204
Let's go.

771
00:52:39,457 --> 00:52:42,793
You're gonna die, mother fucker!
You're gonna fucking die!

772
00:52:53,505 --> 00:52:55,505
None of you motherfuckers can cover me!

773
00:52:55,839 --> 00:52:59,174
We got ourselves a game!
I'm feeling good today.

774
00:52:59,674 --> 00:53:00,840
This shit feels good.

775
00:53:07,885 --> 00:53:08,844
Fuck!

776
00:53:15,262 --> 00:53:17,264
Get the fuck off me!

777
00:53:28,560 --> 00:53:31,352
Yeah, keep smiling, you little piss ant.

778
00:53:34,354 --> 00:53:37,022
For 90 minutes, we took
the game out of the prison...

779
00:53:37,648 --> 00:53:39,564
...moved it miles beyond
the locked gates...

780
00:53:39,731 --> 00:53:41,857
...and the sloping hills of
the surrounding countryside...

781
00:53:42,483 --> 00:53:45,274
...and brought it back down to the streets
of the neighborhoods we'd come from.

782
00:53:46,525 --> 00:53:49,360
For those 90 minutes,
we were once again free!

783
00:54:08,200 --> 00:54:09,701
Rizzo! Rizzo!

784
00:54:21,622 --> 00:54:25,415
Rizzo...Rizzo.

785
00:54:27,124 --> 00:54:30,292
Hey, Nokes.
Good game.

786
00:54:33,211 --> 00:54:36,545
For once, we had a victory.
But it didn't last.

787
00:54:37,212 --> 00:54:41,547
It couldn't last...
and all I wanted to do was die.

788
00:54:42,631 --> 00:54:46,631
I was not alone in the hole. I knew my
friends were down in the depths with me.

789
00:54:47,174 --> 00:54:51,468
Each in his own cell, each in his own
pain...suffering his own demons.

790
00:54:52,093 --> 00:54:53,219
Rizzo was there, too.

791
00:54:56,261 --> 00:54:57,927
I had lost any sense of time.

792
00:55:38,777 --> 00:55:39,945
I thought you'd never wake up.

793
00:55:41,279 --> 00:55:42,613
I thought I'd never want to.

794
00:55:42,987 --> 00:55:46,155
John and Tommy, they're
on the other side there.

795
00:55:47,698 --> 00:55:51,367
How are they?
They're alive.

796
00:55:53,159 --> 00:55:54,160
Who isn't?

797
00:55:56,118 --> 00:55:57,076
Rizzo.

798
00:55:59,786 --> 00:56:00,953
They killed him?

799
00:56:02,953 --> 00:56:07,164
They took turns beating him until
there was nothing of that kid to beat.

800
00:56:12,082 --> 00:56:13,500
Rizzo was dead because of us.

801
00:56:14,916 --> 00:56:16,917
We made him think that going
up against the guards...

802
00:56:17,000 --> 00:56:18,418
...in a meaningless football game...

803
00:56:18,585 --> 00:56:22,169
...had some value...that it would
give us a reason to go on.

804
00:56:23,337 --> 00:56:25,047
Once again, we were wrong.

805
00:56:28,214 --> 00:56:29,548
Did they give you
your release date yet?

806
00:56:29,714 --> 00:56:31,048
Nokes had a letter from the warden.

807
00:56:31,882 --> 00:56:33,759
Waved it in front of me,
then tore it up....

808
00:56:34,925 --> 00:56:35,759
When do you figure?

809
00:56:37,550 --> 00:56:39,760
End of spring, early
summer or something.

810
00:56:40,843 --> 00:56:42,385
I wish we were coming with you.

811
00:56:43,427 --> 00:56:45,763
It would've been nice for all
of us to walk out together.

812
00:56:47,055 --> 00:56:50,389
No use thinking about that. We're
gonna do a full year, not an hour less.

813
00:56:52,432 --> 00:56:55,767
When I get out, I could get Father
Bobby to make a couple of phone calls.

814
00:56:55,975 --> 00:56:57,392
Shave a month or two off.

815
00:56:57,559 --> 00:57:00,226
-There's nothing to talk about!
-There's a lot to talk about.

816
00:57:00,725 --> 00:57:03,645
Maybe, if people knew what was going
on in here, they'd make a move.

817
00:57:04,229 --> 00:57:05,896
I don't want anybody to know.

818
00:57:06,687 --> 00:57:10,397
Not Father Bobby, King Benny,
Fat Mancho...

819
00:57:10,564 --> 00:57:12,898
...not my mother. Nobody.

820
00:57:14,523 --> 00:57:16,066
I don't either.

821
00:57:16,149 --> 00:57:18,399
I mean, I wouldn't know what
to say to anyone who did know.

822
00:57:19,107 --> 00:57:21,778
I can't think of anybody
who needs to hear about it.

823
00:57:22,945 --> 00:57:25,487
Either they won't believe it,
or they won't give a shit.

824
00:57:26,445 --> 00:57:28,739
Yeah, I don't even think we should
talk about it once it's over.

825
00:57:31,072 --> 00:57:35,073
We got no choice but to live with it.
And talking makes living it harder.

826
00:57:36,449 --> 00:57:38,617
So, we might as well
not even talk about it.

827
00:57:39,616 --> 00:57:40,951
The truth stays with us.

828
00:57:44,119 --> 00:57:45,953
I want to be able to sleep one night...

829
00:57:47,494 --> 00:57:51,080
...and not have to worry who's coming
in my room, what's gonna happen to me.

830
00:57:54,830 --> 00:57:58,790
If I can get that, then I'll be happy.

831
00:58:01,460 --> 00:58:04,253
Someday, John, I promise.

832
00:58:20,926 --> 00:58:24,425
I was in my last hours as an inmate
at the Wilkinson Home for boys.

833
00:58:25,261 --> 00:58:27,177
I was given four copies
of my release form.

834
00:58:27,553 --> 00:58:29,845
The final reminder of my
time at Wilkinson.

835
00:58:32,304 --> 00:58:33,888
I never heard the key
turn in the lock...

836
00:58:34,471 --> 00:58:36,556
...and I never heard
the snap of the bolt.

837
00:58:38,057 --> 00:58:39,391
You should be asleep.

838
00:58:40,641 --> 00:58:44,684
I just wanted to say goodbye.
We all do.

839
00:58:47,686 --> 00:58:49,686
I told him. I told him right
to his face. I said,

840
00:58:49,853 --> 00:58:51,687
I don't care if you're paying me
overtime or not.

841
00:58:51,770 --> 00:58:53,312
I'm not working those kind of hours.

842
00:58:53,521 --> 00:58:54,854
Yeah, did you put in for it?

843
00:58:55,354 --> 00:58:56,314
I put in for it!

844
00:58:56,356 --> 00:58:58,064
Because I put in for it.
They don't give it to me.

845
00:58:58,690 --> 00:59:01,899
I come in early for three days.
Do they give me overtime? No!

846
00:59:03,066 --> 00:59:05,026
A part of all of us was
left there that night.

847
00:59:06,068 --> 00:59:08,402
That night will never be
removed from my mind.

848
00:59:08,986 --> 00:59:13,529
The night of June 1, 1968--
the Summer of Love.

849
00:59:15,196 --> 00:59:17,197
My last night at the
Wilkinson Home for boys.

850
01:00:03,966 --> 01:00:06,632
At 8:25 p.m. two men
walked through the doors.

851
01:00:07,632 --> 01:00:10,718
The bartender knew their faces as most
of the neighborhood knew their names.

852
01:00:11,136 --> 01:00:13,761
They were two of the founding
members of the West Side Boys.

853
01:00:13,845 --> 01:00:15,345
They were also its deadliest.

854
01:00:17,429 --> 01:00:20,430
The blond-haired man had been in and out
of jail since he was a teenager.

855
01:00:21,014 --> 01:00:23,097
He robbed and killed
at will or on command.

856
01:00:23,931 --> 01:00:26,599
He was presently a suspect in
four unsolved homicides.

857
01:00:27,182 --> 01:00:30,769
He was an alcoholic and a cocaine abuser
with a fast temper and a faster trigger.

858
01:00:31,227 --> 01:00:34,061
He once shot a mechanic dead for
moving ahead of him in a movie line.

859
01:00:36,353 --> 01:00:38,354
The dark-haired man was equally deadly...

860
01:00:38,396 --> 01:00:40,688
...and had committed his
first murder at the age of 17.

861
01:00:41,563 --> 01:00:45,399
In return, he was paid $50.
He drank, and he did drugs...

862
01:00:45,564 --> 01:00:48,691
...and he had a wife he never saw,
living somewhere in Queens.

863
01:00:51,400 --> 01:00:54,819
He's making a noble attempt
to really change things.

864
01:00:54,903 --> 01:00:58,569
-The Republicans will take the House.
-Well, we got a lot of work to do.

865
01:00:58,694 --> 01:01:00,362
It's gonna take more
than 4 years to get....

866
01:01:00,529 --> 01:01:01,738
They'll take it at
the mid-term elections.

867
01:01:02,238 --> 01:01:05,072
He's got the charisma.
He's gonna do it.

868
01:01:05,282 --> 01:01:07,950
He's our man. Reagan's
the man who's gonna do it.

869
01:01:09,575 --> 01:01:11,784
Hey, Jerry...
What are they talking about?

870
01:01:12,202 --> 01:01:14,201
They're talking about Reagan's speech.

871
01:01:17,202 --> 01:01:19,704
Order those two men some
drinks and put it on my tab.

872
01:01:21,621 --> 01:01:24,455
You tell them that Republicans
are not welcome in Hell's Kitchen...

873
01:01:24,622 --> 01:01:28,123
...and either a political conversion or
a change of conversation is in order.

874
01:01:28,540 --> 01:01:29,541
Sure thing.

875
01:01:36,584 --> 01:01:39,503
The gentlemen there would like to
buy you a drink on one condition.

876
01:01:39,794 --> 01:01:43,504
You know the rules:
no religion, no politics.

877
01:01:44,128 --> 01:01:45,255
You get my meaning?

878
01:02:03,137 --> 01:02:05,430
Order something for me.
I gotta go to the bathroom.

879
01:02:36,274 --> 01:02:37,400
Can I help you with something, chief?

880
01:02:39,276 --> 01:02:43,654
Not right now.
Enjoy the rest of your meal.

881
01:03:29,713 --> 01:03:33,921
I ordered brisket on a roll,
with fries and...

882
01:03:35,339 --> 01:03:38,090
...two baskets of soda bread.
I know how you like that shit.

883
01:03:39,218 --> 01:03:40,218
Is that okay by you?

884
01:03:42,592 --> 01:03:45,677
Take a look at the guy at the table.
Take a good look.

885
01:03:57,517 --> 01:03:58,599
Motherfucker.

886
01:04:25,110 --> 01:04:26,693
That's him.

887
01:04:26,985 --> 01:04:28,402
Are you fucking kidding me?

888
01:04:31,945 --> 01:04:32,653
Bingo!

889
01:04:58,373 --> 01:04:59,497
This is amazing.

890
01:04:59,665 --> 01:05:02,333
Hello...it's been a long time!

891
01:05:04,083 --> 01:05:05,167
Who the fuck are you guys?

892
01:05:09,543 --> 01:05:11,127
Who the fuck asked you to sit down?

893
01:05:11,627 --> 01:05:14,713
I thought you'd be happy to see us.
I guess I was wrong.

894
01:05:16,547 --> 01:05:18,964
You know, I thought
you'd do a lot better.

895
01:05:19,632 --> 01:05:21,841
You know, with all that training...
all that time you put in...

896
01:05:22,466 --> 01:05:24,507
...just to end up watching
someone else's money.

897
01:05:24,842 --> 01:05:26,134
That seems like a waste.

898
01:05:26,342 --> 01:05:28,300
I'm asking you now for the last
time, what the fuck do you want?

899
01:05:28,508 --> 01:05:30,217
Why don't you take your time?
It'll come to you.

900
01:05:36,013 --> 01:05:37,806
I can see how he might forget us.

901
01:05:38,472 --> 01:05:41,389
You know, we were just something for
you and your friends to play with.

902
01:05:41,556 --> 01:05:43,682
It's a little harder for us to forget.

903
01:05:44,057 --> 01:05:46,309
You gave us so much more to remember.

904
01:05:49,683 --> 01:05:51,060
You can't quite place us,
can you, chief?

905
01:05:51,810 --> 01:05:55,812
Let me help you out. You're looking
at John Reilly and Tommy Marcano.

906
01:06:07,275 --> 01:06:08,191
Yeah, that's right.

907
01:06:14,985 --> 01:06:16,321
That was a long time ago.

908
01:06:19,862 --> 01:06:20,614
So how you been?

909
01:06:21,614 --> 01:06:23,114
Yeah, we ain't kids now.

910
01:06:24,406 --> 01:06:25,740
So, what do you want?

911
01:06:26,573 --> 01:06:29,909
What I've always wanted
is to watch you die!

912
01:06:35,954 --> 01:06:36,995
You ordered the meat loaf.

913
01:06:38,621 --> 01:06:41,622
The brisket's really good here,
only you'll never know it.

914
01:06:42,914 --> 01:06:43,746
You fucked up.

915
01:06:57,545 --> 01:07:01,879
Yeah, you were scared little pricks,
both of you.

916
01:07:03,421 --> 01:07:08,091
All of you...scared shitless.
But l...

917
01:07:10,009 --> 01:07:13,467
...l tried to make you tough.
I tried to make you hard.

918
01:07:13,508 --> 01:07:17,136
I had you all wrong then, Nokes.
All this time I thought you just liked...

919
01:07:17,302 --> 01:07:18,803
...fucking and beating up little boys.

920
01:07:19,011 --> 01:07:21,262
You two motherfuckers
are gonna burn in hell!

921
01:07:21,845 --> 01:07:23,179
You're gonna burn in hell.

922
01:07:23,347 --> 01:07:24,303
Yeah, after you.

923
01:07:30,099 --> 01:07:31,267
Did that hurt, Nokes?

924
01:08:08,782 --> 01:08:13,033
Jerry, sorry, should've made
those brisket sandwiches to go.

925
01:08:25,621 --> 01:08:26,955
John Reilly, how do you plead?

926
01:08:27,330 --> 01:08:28,497
Not guilty, Your Honor.

927
01:08:29,455 --> 01:08:30,332
Thomas Marcano?

928
01:08:31,831 --> 01:08:33,000
Not guilty, Your Honor.

929
01:08:33,539 --> 01:08:37,251
John Reilly and Thomas Marcano,
you are hereby held without bail.

930
01:08:38,458 --> 01:08:41,878
In all the years since Wilkinson's, we
had never once spoken to each other...

931
01:08:42,043 --> 01:08:45,379
...about what happened there.
We remained caring friends...

932
01:08:45,546 --> 01:08:47,546
...but the relationship
had been altered.

933
01:08:48,714 --> 01:08:52,883
We drifted together, always wondering
if that moment would arrive...

934
01:08:53,339 --> 01:08:55,090
...that would force us to
deal with the past.

935
01:09:08,597 --> 01:09:11,930
One down, Shakes, one down.

936
01:09:13,931 --> 01:09:14,763
One what?

937
01:09:17,016 --> 01:09:20,350
One Sean Nokes.

938
01:09:21,518 --> 01:09:22,393
Nokes?

939
01:09:30,687 --> 01:09:31,937
At the time of Nokes' shooting,

940
01:09:31,979 --> 01:09:34,938
Michael was working as an
Assistant New York District Attorney.

941
01:09:35,732 --> 01:09:38,484
I got a call that he wanted to meet me
on 45th Street in Queens.

942
01:09:39,317 --> 01:09:40,275
Then, he hung up.

943
01:09:44,818 --> 01:09:46,528
-So, what did they say?
-What?

944
01:09:46,778 --> 01:09:48,028
John and Tommy, what'd they say?

945
01:09:48,196 --> 01:09:49,529
It's a little cloak and
dagger, isn't it, Mike?

946
01:09:50,446 --> 01:09:52,447
Nokes?
Did they talk about him?

947
01:09:54,363 --> 01:09:55,698
-John did.
-Yeah?

948
01:09:56,573 --> 01:09:57,573
What did he say?

949
01:09:58,407 --> 01:10:01,034
He said, "One down, Shakes.
One down."

950
01:10:04,576 --> 01:10:06,577
I hear they hired Danny Snyder
as the lawyer, is that right?

951
01:10:06,745 --> 01:10:09,244
It's temporary. King Benny's
gonna move in one of his lawyers.

952
01:10:09,495 --> 01:10:12,162
Don't let him do that.
Snyder's perfect.

953
01:10:12,413 --> 01:10:14,789
-Perfect? The guy's a fall down drunk!
-Then he is perfect.

954
01:10:15,290 --> 01:10:16,414
Perfect for what?

955
01:10:20,458 --> 01:10:22,292
Are you covering this
story for your newspaper?

956
01:10:22,459 --> 01:10:23,459
-Me?
-Yeah.

